"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-voices-olympics-paris-bob-ballard-women-sexism-b2587634.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Veteran Games commentator Bob Ballard has rightly been removed from duty after comments about Australia's record-breaking relay swimmers - but there is a good reason why misogynist small talk is so noticeable at Paris 2024, saysGemma Abbott  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 563, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 242, \"end\": 245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"score\": 0.7149176451483255, \"rank\": 0.2908733849029316, \"text\": \"Bob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\"}, {\"begin\": 246, \"end\": 253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"score\": 0.9999999912261046, \"rank\": 8.773813769156094e-09, \"text\": \"Ballard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\"}, {\"begin\": 310, \"end\": 319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999742273090956, \"rank\": 1.9091642420419925e-05, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  When organisers of theParis Olympicsdecided to bill it as the\\\"equal Games\\\"- in celebration of the fact that, for the first time, women make up 50 per cent of the competitors - the claim was always going to come in for scrutiny.\", \"from\": 564, \"to\": 815, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But it found itself severely tested onday two, and by a commentator who should have known better.\", \"from\": 817, \"to\": 914, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Having secured gold in thewomen's 4x100m freestyle relay, the Australian quartet of Emma McKeon, Shayna Jack, Mollie O'Callaghan and Meg Harris made their way out of the Paris Aquatic Centre.\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 1107, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 978, \"end\": 988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999995986964573, \"rank\": 4.00824199255924e-07, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 1000, \"end\": 1011, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_McKeon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emma McKeon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_McKeon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_McKeon\"}, {\"begin\": 1013, \"end\": 1024, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shayna_Jack\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shayna Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shayna_Jack\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shayna_Jack\"}, {\"begin\": 1026, \"end\": 1044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mollie_O'Callaghan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mollie O'Callaghan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mollie_O'Callaghan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mollie_O'Callaghan\"}, {\"begin\": 1049, \"end\": 1059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meg_Harris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Meg Harris\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meg_Harris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meg_Harris\"}, {\"begin\": 1086, \"end\": 1091, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999956344254, \"rank\": 4.365474155210831e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was then thatEurosport commentator Bob Ballardsaid: \\\"Well, the women, just finishing up.\", \"from\": 1108, \"to\": 1199, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1146, \"end\": 1149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"score\": 0.7149176451483255, \"rank\": 0.2908733849029316, \"text\": \"Bob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You know what women are like\\u2026 hanging around, doing their makeup\\u2026\\\"  The outrageous comment went viral instantly, and Ballard was subsequently removed from Eurosport's broadcasting roster.\", \"from\": 1200, \"to\": 1387, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1317, \"end\": 1324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"score\": 0.9999999912261046, \"rank\": 8.773813769156094e-09, \"text\": \"Ballard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\"}, {\"begin\": 1355, \"end\": 1364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurosport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4822632793192977e-17, \"text\": \"Eurosport\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurosport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurosport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports commentary is an art form.\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1422, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It takes a sharp mind and a keen eye to encapsulate a moment for an audience, to translate the action in a sports arena to the listener or viewer.\", \"from\": 1423, \"to\": 1569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ballard has had a long and successful career in commentating.\", \"from\": 1571, \"to\": 1632, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1571, \"end\": 1578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"score\": 0.9999999912261046, \"rank\": 8.773813769156094e-09, \"text\": \"Ballard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The BBC has described him as \\\"a stalwart of global sports coverage since the 1980s, reporting on multiple Olympic Games and world championships\\\".\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1778, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1637, \"end\": 1640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.9999337355453211, \"rank\": 5.00179445738997e-05, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, with all that experience behind him, what part of Ballard suddenly made him feel it was acceptable to make such an obviously sexist comment?\", \"from\": 1780, \"to\": 1924, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1834, \"end\": 1841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"score\": 0.9999999912261046, \"rank\": 8.773813769156094e-09, \"text\": \"Ballard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Misogynist language is not new to the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1926, \"to\": 1973, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"During the Rio Games in 2016,Mail Onlinedescribed American swimmer Katie Ledecky as \\\"the female Michael Phelps\\\".\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 2086, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2041, \"end\": 2054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}, {\"begin\": 2070, \"end\": 2084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.194412964554915e-55, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WhenUS gymnast Simone Bilesgave an incredible performance on the uneven bars, an NBC commentator gave a backhanded compliment, saying: \\\"I think she might even go higher than the men.\\\"\", \"from\": 2087, \"to\": 2270, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2168, \"end\": 2171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.998917675219055, \"rank\": 0.001083496271269805, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some comedians appear to think that female Olympians are fair game.\", \"from\": 2272, \"to\": 2339, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the 2012 London Games, US TV host Conan O'Brien tweeted that weightlifter Holley Mangold would \\\"bring home the gold- and four guys against their will\\\".\", \"from\": 2340, \"to\": 2494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2377, \"end\": 2382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conan_the_Barbarian\", \"score\": 0.9999999912183739, \"rank\": 8.781423266384323e-09, \"text\": \"Conan\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conan_the_Barbarian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conan_the_Barbarian\"}, {\"begin\": 2417, \"end\": 2431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holley_Mangold\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Holley Mangold\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holley_Mangold\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holley_Mangold\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And it was during Beijing 2008 thatFrankie Boylefirst made his now infamous jibes about gold-medal swimmerRebecca Adlington, saying she \\\"looks pretty weird... like someone who's looking at themselves in the back of a spoon\\\".\", \"from\": 2495, \"to\": 2719, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2513, \"end\": 2525, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999995375219, \"rank\": 4.624303255091881e-10, \"text\": \"Beijing 2008\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2609, \"end\": 2618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adlington_Hall\", \"score\": 0.9999917386944804, \"rank\": 6.313147560071048e-06, \"text\": \"Adlington\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adlington_Hall\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adlington_Hall\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to a study by Cambridge University Press, sexist thinking runs through the Games.\", \"from\": 2721, \"to\": 2812, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2745, \"end\": 2771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"score\": 0.9319011684590155, \"rank\": 0.07307516488427633, \"text\": \"Cambridge University Press\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Researchers analysed millions of words relating to men and women and Olympic sports in the Cambridge international corpus (CIC) and the sports corpus - enormous databases of news articles and social media posts.\", \"from\": 2813, \"to\": 3024, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2936, \"end\": 2939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Information_Commission\", \"score\": 0.974142566594674, \"rank\": 0.01164680450662347, \"text\": \"CIC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Information_Commission\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Information_Commission\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The study found that language around female competitors focussed disproportionately on appearance, clothes and personal lives.\", \"from\": 3025, \"to\": 3151, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Common word combinations for women included \\\"aged\\\", \\\"older\\\", \\\"pregnant\\\" and \\\"married\\\" or \\\"unmarried\\\".\", \"from\": 3152, \"to\": 3253, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In contrast, top word combinations for male athletes included \\\"fastest\\\", \\\"strong\\\", \\\"big\\\" and \\\"great\\\".\", \"from\": 3254, \"to\": 3355, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I can think of several common examples of such casual sexism in sports reporting.\", \"from\": 3357, \"to\": 3438, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you listen out for it, you will hear the word \\\"girls\\\" often used as a descriptor of women competing in sport.\", \"from\": 3439, \"to\": 3551, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But can you remember the last time you heard a group of sportsmen being referred to as boys?\", \"from\": 3552, \"to\": 3644, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Likewise, when certain sports are discussed in the media, it is often assumed that the sport being mentioned in the report is the men's game.\", \"from\": 3646, \"to\": 3787, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How often do we hear the media refer to \\\"women's football\\\", whereas men's football is just \\\"football\\\"?\", \"from\": 3788, \"to\": 3890, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the dial has definitely moved.\", \"from\": 3892, \"to\": 3931, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The proportion of female athletes competing has increased in every Olympic Games since 1964, when it was 13.2 per cent.\", \"from\": 3932, \"to\": 4051, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By Rio 2016, it was 45 per cent.\", \"from\": 4052, \"to\": 4084, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Only now do we finally have a 50:50 ratio.\", \"from\": 4085, \"to\": 4127, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Female participation in sports has increased, making the media more aware of its responsibility when covering female athletes.\", \"from\": 4129, \"to\": 4255, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The fact that major broadcasters such as Eurosport act swiftly when Ballardisms occur is proof of real progress.\", \"from\": 4256, \"to\": 4368, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As coverage improves, sexist language and comments are more noticeable when they happen.\", \"from\": 4369, \"to\": 4457, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I bet this will not be the last bit of casual sexism we hear during these Olympics.\", \"from\": 4459, \"to\": 4546, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Viewers, on your marks\\u2026  Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 4547, \"to\": 4802, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4623, \"end\": 4634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3375816258496497e-22, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}]}"